		<div id="comment_body_64169393"><p>This is one thing I have serious issues with myself. If I have read something in a book I have a rough idea about how deep in the book it was, and a general 'shape' of the text on that page; was it very densely written, or lots of small paragraphs like quick dialogue in a novel?</p><p>I can't use that when scrolling through eg. a large PDF. There's something about the way the next page of text appears in exactly the same spot as the previous page that messes with my mental image of what I am looking for. In a book<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
